According to a report by Intel Market Research, the Europe Sneaker Market was valued at USD 21.24 billion in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 22.82 billion in 2026 to USD 35.48 billion by 2034, registering a CAGR of 7.8% during the forecast period. The market is experiencing strong growth due to rising health consciousness, increasing participation in sports and fitness activities, and the continued popularity of athleisure fashion across Europe. Growing consumer preference for sustainable footwear, limited-edition collaborations, and expanding e-commerce platforms are further accelerating market expansion.
